NINE people were killed in a crash on the N2 between Makhanda and Nanaga, Eastern Cape, on Sunday, 10 January. According to authorities, a fully loaded taxi travelling towards Gqeberha collided with another taxi travelling in the opposite direction with only two occupants. The taxi with the two occupants was driven by a husband and wife. They both died in the collision, along with seven people from the other taxi. “One Quantum was from PE to Mthatha, with only two occupants and the other one was from Tsolo to Mossel Bay, fully loaded,” said Eastern Cape transport spokesman Unathi Binqose. The deceased include three adult females, four men and two kids aged one and four. The injured were rushed to hospital in Makhanda and a culpable homicide docket has been opened.